</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFB9BA15B4A1F316B190FAC0" pageId="5" pageNumber="624" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="915436DFFFB9BA15B4A1F316B190FAC0" blockId="5.[177,1384,717,1334]" pageId="5" pageNumber="624">
<emphasis id="A39FEACDFFB9BA15B4A1F316B03EFB59" bold="true" box="[179,536,1142,1175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="624">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List. The Incan Little Mastiff Bat is listed as critically endangered on the national Red List of 
<collectingCountry id="E9FC764FFFB9BA15B0F1F3FEB701FB71" box="[1251,1319,1182,1215]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="624">Peru</collectingCountry>
. Itis known from only three specimens at or near type locality, which is located in a national protected area (Santuario historico de Machu Picchu).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
